Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.
.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.
.

The first thing I noticed about this photo were my crows feet & other wrinkles around my eyes 👵🏼 Those wrinkles are the result of yearssss worth of laughter, smiles, and joy! And that’s exactly what I noticed next…our smiles 😊

I’ve been honest about how how difficult it’s been to parent Ella. I believe she has an underlying diagnosis, but don’t know what. Moments like these are few and far between with her. But the day we took this photo was a GOOD day 😍 We were having the best time together! I cherish every moment like this with her because they give me so much hope. So f*ck the wrinkles! I’m posting the photo because our joy far outweighs the creases, crinkles, and lines of my last 40 years 😁

node.text:
As we re-introduce ourselves to some of our new friends here on Instagram, I thought it would be fun to highlight one of our furry family members…Ariel 🐕 She’s the one in the middle btw 😂

I adopted Ariel from a rescue called Lucky Labs in Austin, TX. My dog Piper had recently passed (I had her for 13 1/2 years) and I was grieving HARD 😭 I didn’t think I could trust another dog around my kids and worried about their safety. Then I met the dog with the saddest eyes I’d ever seen. Ariel was picked up somewhere in the valley. She was pregnant with 5 pups and completely emaciated. The first time we met she came right up to me. She looked so tired and starved. But she was gentle, loving, and so sweet.

Fast forward 3 years and she’s healthy, happy, and loves doing zoomies all over the house 🤣 It’s clear she was not treated well by whoever had her before the rescue took her out of the shelter. She’s terrified of men, struggles with anxiety, and is fearful of new people who enter our home. It breaks my heart to see her scared & one of us is always there to reassure and comfort her. We’ve built a lot of trust with one another and she’s learning that mom will never let anyone hurt her again 💗 We love you, Ariel aka Air Bear aka Bear aka Bearsy!

Gimme a WOOF 🐶 in the comments if you love your pets like full blown family 🐾

𝑩𝒖𝒕 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒄𝒐𝒎𝒆 𝒃𝒂𝒄𝒌 𝒕𝒐 𝒘𝒉𝒂𝒕 𝒚𝒐𝒖 𝒏𝒆𝒆𝒅 ✨

I used to tell Emaya that this song always reminded me of her. Every time she left my heart shattered into a million pieces 💔 In those moments, I felt a very small piece of the pain she’d known all her life. Grief, rejection, loss, and that feeling of trying to hold onto something that always felt like it might fall away from you at any given time.

I know this text is a little different from the photos you’ve been seeing and the videos we used to post. But this is us. Our family didn’t start with positive pregnancy tests, cute ultrasound photos, or joyous congratulations. We were connected through whatever entity you want to believe in and we held on to one another for dear life. And it was HARD!

I will never portray us as the perfect family. We’re are absolutely the opposite. And we drive each other nuts most of the time. Eli, Evan, and Ella have grown up only knowing me as their mother. They know I love them because I WANT to not because I have to. Emaya is slowly learning that concept & it tears me apart that the “love” she’s known in her life always came with stipulations.

I’m working hard to teach her that she owes me NOTHING and this is how a parent-child relationship should work. I hope all my children know what an honor and a privilege it’s been to be their mom. The road we’ve traveled separately and together has not been an easy one, but I’d walk it all over again if it meant doing life with the same incredible humans who have given me the title I value most…mom ❤️‍🔥

My children will always be the greatest loves of my life 🌈

It’s the kind of tan that only exists on your feet (making them look dirty rather than deliciously golden brown from wearing flip flops too often) and from the elbow down 🤣 I’d be embarrassed, but I left that emotion in the dust back around age 36ish 😁 While I can’t wait for the Fall, I know I’m going to miss warm days at the beach.

What’s everyone’s favorite season and WHY? The why is the most important part. I’m guessing we have a LOT of fellow Fall fans out there 🍁🎃

I love how much Evan and Ella love Eli 💙 I love that neither of them sees severe disabilities as something “different” or “unusual.” They understand that Eli is unable to walk and when they play with him they get down on the ground with him. Sometimes they’ll even lay right next to him carrying on random conversations as if Eli is their own personal therapist 😂

Our family is incredibly diverse! A fact that I honestly sometimes forget. It’s often not until someone comments on how “unique” we are (that’s a polite way of saying a rag tag team of misfits 😂) that I stop to think about just how diverse we are not only as individuals, but especially as a whole.

I love that our family is woven together by so many distinct characteristics and factors. We’re a colorful bunch, to say the least and we def check off EVERY box! LGBTQ+ ☑️ Multi-ethnic ☑️ Disabilities ☑️ Single Parent Family ☑️ Adoptive Family ☑️ and that’s just listing a few of them 😁 Truth be told, I LOVE that we’re all so different ❣️ Life’s a lot more interesting this way! The McLeod’s don’t do cookie cutter, that’s for sure 😉

The greatest gift I could ever give each of them…was the other 💞

I know we have a lot of new friends here on IG and I’ve been getting the same question a LOT! “Are Ella and Evan biological siblings?” The answer is YES! I do not know if they share the same biological father and will eventually have them tested to figure that out. For now, they’re just happy and little and have no in depth understanding that their connection is a little different from that of their other siblings.

In our home LOVE MAKES A FAMILY 🌈 I have worked hard to teach my children that family are the people who are there for you through thick and thin. Family does not manipulate or abuse you. Family does not make you feel as if you have an obligation to allow them space in your life. Family isn’t perfect. Family is love NOT DNA. Family should not be toxic. Family does not treat you like a second class citizen. Family accepts you, loves you, supports you, and encourages you. We ARE family ❤️🧡💛💚💙💜🖤🤍
